SUMMARY:Calling on the Widow
DESCRIPTION:Pay your respects to T.C. Steele’s widow, Selma, when you call at the House of the Singing Winds. Learn to write a sympathy note, fashion a black armband to wear, visit with the widow, and leave a flower on Steele’s grave as we explore a 1920s mourning practices. Finish your visit with a stop in Steele’s Large Studio as we honor 100 years of the painter’s impact in Brown County and beyond.\n
URL:https://browncounty.com/events/calling-on-the-widow/
ORGANIZER;CN=T.C.Steele State Historic Site:MAILTO:tcsteeleshs@indianamuseum.org
CATEGORIES:Special Events
